A zen rock garden viewed from above, with carefully raked sand forming concentric ripples around smooth dark stones, but one section of the garden transitions into an organized grid of small compartments containing miniature objects representing tasks - tiny scrolls, tools, and symbols. The contrast between the serene empty spaces and the methodically organized elements creates visual tension. Soft morning light casts long shadows across the sand patterns. Studio Ghibli style with warm muted colors, gentle watercolor textures, and that distinctive hand-painted quality with visible brushstrokes in the sky and subtle magical atmosphere in the way light particles float through the air.
